Title: ðŸ“Œ [ANN] ðŸ“¢ [ICO] ðŸ’° COINVEST ðŸ“ˆ DECENTRALIZED STOCK MARKET FOR CRYPTOCURRENCIES ðŸ“Š
Body: Hi Udonmez - We aren't a decentralized exchange (at least not until we execute our full vision).    We are a trading platform run and managed by smart contracts.  Consider us a decentralized E-Trade for cryptocurrencies.  Our difference and main advantage is that we are decentralized. Our investment process is managed by smart contracts including user investment data and funds.  User funds are held in escrow by the smart contract until they are withdrawn by the user. Coinvest has no ability to touch or manage those funds including the liquidity pool that collateralize and back the investments. Once funds are withdrawn from a userâ€™s portfolio, they can be stored in the wallet or spent using the built-in debit account.  Additionally the following: -  Diversification:  Coinvest enables you to curate your own personal index fund (In the future, we will allow users to invest into other user's personal index funds.) -  Simplicity and Speed:  No KYC requirements and validation as we don't deal with Fiat currency -  Convenience:   Invest in multiple cryptonized assets without having to worry about storage, multiple wallets, multiple private keys, and transferring / supporting all coin protocols -  Functionality:  Coinvest enables flexible trading options to help you obtain the best value with buy, buy limit, short orders -  Cost:  Since Coinvest is automated and controlled by smart contracts, third-parties and overhead are removed which leads to lower cost transactions fees  For a complete and detailed comparison, we recommend you view pages 7 and 8 of our whitepaper at: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ePI50Vd9MGdkPnH0KdVuhTOOSiqmnE7WteGDtG10GuE/edit?usp=sharing  Thanks!

Body: No.  Debevoise & Plimpton (along with Cooley)  are just contributors that created this framework for companies to test and determine if they are a security?  Out of complete transparency, (because these are our values), we have not secured an official formal relationship with a legal counsel yet.  We have had preliminary conversations with legal counsel and will look to formalize a relationship once our pre-sale concludes (since they are not cheap  ).  In preliminary discussions and based upon our parameters / results in this framework, we feel very strongly and confident that we are not considered a security.  We recommend viewing lines 9 - 18 of that document for specific reasons why.  Thanks!

Body: Coinvest is creating a future where users have one platform, one wallet, and one token (COIN), that enables anyone to create a digital investment portfolio to invest in multiple cryptocurrencies. Thereby reducing the cost, risk, and complexity associated with investing in cryptocurrencies on centralized exchanges or investment funds. Centralized third parties that are often needed in traditional investment use cases are replaced with smart contracts that act as autonomous agents and programmatically compensate all users, investors, and owners within the entire Coinvest ecosystem.

Body: Hi Bigcash!  Investors benefit from value appreciation in the COIN itself.  Unfortunately we are not a security and do not offer profit sharing, dividends, or returns for investors.  However, 50% of company net profit will be leveraged to replenish the COIN reserve in the smart contract and for buybacks of COIN in order to ensure price stability and token asset holder value.  As more participants join the ecosystem, the community rapidly increases in size through network effects. As the overall ecosystem grows, transaction volumes increase requiring the need for COIN token purchases to fund smart contract execution. In turn, the value of the COIN token will appreciate organically through demand. But most importantly, community transactions increase and become perpetual.

Body: You get to decide and control the distributions % of your own personal index fund.    Suppose you want to buy 10 different COINS on an exchange, you would have to purchase each one individually and incur fees for each transaction, manage wallet storage for each different protocols, manage multiple, private keys, etc.  On Coinvest, you can complete this in one trade, only incur a $4.99 trading fee, and don't have to worry about the things above.  In the future, other users can invest into your own index fund (and you can essentially become a "hedge fund" manager).

Body: Thansk Consigliere!  As previously noted, we vary greatly with our competition. More specifically, no other platform enables you to curate your own personal index fund. (In the future, we will allow users to invest into other user's personal index funds as well)  Our largest advantage is that we are decentralized. Our investment process is managed by smart contracts including user investment data and funds.  User funds are held in escrow by the smart contract until they are withdrawn by the user. Coinvest has no ability to touch or manage those funds including the liquidity pool that collateralize and back the investments. Once funds are withdrawn from a userâ€™s portfolio, they can be stored in the wallet or spent using the built-in debit account.  For a complete and detailed comparison, we recommend you view pages 7 and 8 of our whitepaper at: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ePI50Vd9MGdkPnH0KdVuhTOOSiqmnE7WteGDtG10GuE/edit?usp=sharing

Body: Thanks for the feedback here Allan!  Our fee schedule is $4.99 upon any trade order within an investment portfolio. This is significantly lower and more predictable than the fees incurred with competing exchanges.  For example, popular exchanges charge anywhere from .25 - 3% on all transactions regardless of amount or volume.  As a result, a $5,000 order and 1% fee can result in an expense of $50.  Since eveything is autonomous and controlled by smart contracts, we have considerably less overhead than our competition and can offer significantly less fees to support the platform.  Company profits enable us to purchase additional COIN in order to help provide price stability in the market as well.  As for security, our source code will be open-sourced and available for the community to validate and review.  We are using the support of the community (with bug bounties) and will engage two professional security firms to audit our code to ensure the security of the platform.  From a technical perspective, we've partnered with Civic for authentication and will also offer 2FA as an option.  We'll also employ SSL across all public facing channels, etc.  We use AWS but also deploy firewalls to protect databases, etc.  There a more technical things we are doing, but these are just a few examples.

Body: WEBSITE  WHITEPAPER  TELEGRAM  DISCORD TWITTER  FACEBOOK  BLOG    Whitelist Opportunities Available Now      Coinvest is the worldâ€™s first decentralized stock market for cryptocurrencies. We are determined to democratize cryptocurrencies by creating tools to provide mechanisms for consumers to seamlessly, securely, and safely invest and use cryptocurrencies.   Coinvest is creating a future where users have one platform, one wallet, and one token (COIN), that enables anyone to create a digital investment portfolio to invest in multiple cryptocurrencies. Thereby reducing the cost, risk, and complexity associated with investing in cryptocurrencies on centralized exchanges or investment funds. Centralized third parties that are often needed in traditional investment use cases are replaced with smart contracts that act as autonomous agents and programmatically compensate all users, investors, and owners within the entire Coinvest ecosystem.  Please visit https://coinve.st for information regarding Coinvest and our upcoming crowdsale.  Todayâ€™s announcement represents the beginning of a much larger and broader vision.  We are excited to work with the community to create the default platform that will help users seamlessly invest and use cryptocurrencies.  We encourage you to join our Discord and view our website to learn more.   For security, please note:  Coinvest only has one official website (https://coinve.st).  All other websites representing Coinvest and our name should be considered fraudulent and disregarded. Body: Hi Maronk -  Yes... Since we are leveraging smart contracts and our token is based upon the ERC20 ETH standard, that is technically correct.  However, our platform is limited to our COIN token for investment transactions and will require our COIN tokem to operate.  Withdrawals can be requested at any time and are executed by the smart contract.  There is never any involvement with our company or any third-party.  Investments including profit will be withdrawn in COIN tokens and sent back to your wallet.  Thus enabling faster trading and execution which helps frequent and day traders.

Body: Hi Krezz - Profits that users incur from profitable trades will be compensated in COIN tokens as well.  The smart contract will automatically distribute COIN from the COIN reserve back to your wallet.  Our wallet has integration with our partner, Changelly to exchange COIN into any other supported cryptocurrency such as BTC, BCH, and ETH.  Long term, we will integrate debit card support so that you can spend your COIN at any merchant that accepts a debit card.
